{
  "texts": [
    "There were no significant differences between intervention and control conditions in terms of marital status, race, number of children, military rank, and age.",
    "We did find differences for military tenure (in years) and educational status (both of which were higher in the Intervention vs. control condition).",
    "However, in multilevel models, which accounted for clustering by unit, these differences (which appear to reflect differences between units) were no longer significant.",
    "Women had a greater likelihood of being in the treatment vs. control condition (n=16 or 63.6% vs n=8 or 36.4%, respectively).",
    "Conversely, men were disproportionately represented in the control condition (59% vs. 41%), C 2 (1, 266) = 4.229, p <.05."
  ]
}